Former United Nations Secretary General, Kofi Atta Annan, died on Saturday, August 18, 2018 in a hospital in Bern, Switzerland. Annan, a Nobel Peace Prize laureate, was the 7th secretary general of the UN. He was the first UN secretary general who rose through the ranks to be elected head of the global body. Annan served as UN secretary general between 1997 and 2006. Here are some images of his global stewardship:                            